author: CNN
description: Hall of Famer and current head coach of the Portland Trail Blazers, Chauncey Billups, pleaded not guilty in a New York courtroom on Monday to charges stemming from a poker scheme that prosecutors allege helped lure unsuspecting gamblers to a mob-run poker game. CNN’s Mark Morales reports
title: Chauncey Billups pleads not guilty to crimes stemming from alleged poker scheme

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kasie Hunt hosts Miles Taylor, former Chief of Staff for Department of Homeland Security during the first Trump administration, to discuss a federal judge dismissing the indictments against former FBI Director James Comey and New York Attorney General Letitia James. #CNN #News
title: 'A body blow for the rule of law': Ex-Trump official slams President's power to investigate critics

author: CNN
description: New York Giants interim head coach Mike Kafka has fired defensive coordinator Shane Bowen—just two weeks after Brian Daboll was let go. CNN's Coy Wire breaks down the latest shakeup.
title: NY Giants fire defensive coordinator after overtime loss to Lions

author: CNN
description:
The European counter-proposal to the United States’ 28-point peace plan to end the war in Ukraine “at first glance, is completely unconstructive and doesn’t suit us,” Kremlin foreign policy aide Yury Ushakov said Monday, according to Russian state media.

Zain Asher and Bianna Golodryga speak with CNN State Department reporter Jennifer Hansler and CNN military analyst and retired Air Force Col. Cedric Leighton about the status of the war and the peace talks. #CNN #News
title: Kremlin: European counterproposal to US plan 'unconstructive'

author: CNN
description: CNN's Anna Cooban visits London's New Bond Street, where retail real estate is the priciest in the world.
title: London street named world's most expensive retail destination

author: CNN
description: The White House has postponed its rollout of a new proposal to address health care costs aimed at averting a spike in premiums driven by the expiration of key Affordable Care Act subsidies, a White House official said. President Donald Trump was originally expected to unveil the plan on Monday, but now that is not happening. The official did not provide a reason for the delay.  #CNN #News
title: White House postpones expected unveiling of Trump’s health care cost proposal

author: CNN
description: A federal judge dismissed the indictments against former FBI Director James Comey and New York Attorney General Letitia James, ruling that the appointment of Trump's handpicked interim US Attorney Lindsey Halligan was invalid. CNN's Katelyn Polantz explains.
title: Judge throws out cases against James Comey and Letitia James

author: CNN
description: First lady Melania Trump welcomed the official White House Christmas tree, a concolor fir which hails from Korson’s Tree Farms in Sidney, Michigan, and will be the centerpiece of the Blue Room. #CNN #News
title: Melania Trump receives White House Christmas tree

author: CNN
description: A federal judge dismissed the indictments against former FBI Director James Comey and New York Attorney General Letitia James. The judge found that the appointment of interim US Attorney Lindsey Halligan in Alexandria, Virginia, was invalid. Trump handpicked Halligan for the role amid increasing pressure to bring criminal cases against his political enemies, including Comey and James.  #CNN #News
title: Judge throws out cases against James Comey and Letitia James

author: CNN
description:
Nearly 82 million Americans are expected to travel for the Thanksgiving holiday this week, with the Transportation Security Administration expecting more than 17 million people to pass through airport screening checkpoints.

CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with Hayley Berg, lead economist at Hopper, and CNN aviation correspondent Pete Muntean reports on the holiday travel rush. #CNN #News
title: Airlines brace for Thanksgiving rush after weeks of turbulence

author: CNN
description: The announcement of the Bezos’ as sponsors of the 2026 Met Gala drew immediate criticism on social media. Here’s how Anna Wintour responded.
title: Anna Wintour responds to backlash around Bezos sponsorship of Met Gala

author: CNN
description: As US and Ukrainian delegations and EU leaders meet in Geneva to discuss peace plans between Ukraine and Russia, CNN's Matthew Chance analyzes whether this is the beginning of the end of the Ukraine war. #CNN #news
title: Analysis: Could US talks in Geneva bring peace in Ukraine?

author: CNN
description:
Jimmy Cliff, the singer who helped popularize the reggae genre, has died at age 81, his wife announced on Instagram on Monday. “It’s with profound sadness that I share that my husband, Jimmy Cliff, has crossed over due to a seizure followed by pneumonia,” Latifa Chambers said.

#cnn #news #jimmycliff #rockandrollhalloffame #reggae #jamaica
title: Reggae legend Jimmy Cliff dead at 81

author: CNN
description: Kate Bolduan and CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten discuss the holiday shopping season kicking off this week, as millions of Americans are bracing for sticker shock from tariffs and inflation this time around. A Pew Research survey finds that 74% of Americans believe the economy is in fair or poor shape, and CNN's Audie Cornish discusses it with her "Group Chat" panel. CNN's John Berman speaks with University of Michigan professor of economics and public policy Justin Wolfers on recent Trump administration statements on the economy. #CNN #News
title: Americans and the economy: Harry Enten runs the numbers

author: CNN
description: The United Kingdom, France and Germany had drafted a counter-proposal to the US plan with an array of key changes, Reuters has reported. A European official and a European diplomatic source confirmed the text’s accuracy to CNN’s Chief International Security Correspondent Nick Paton Walsh.  #CNN #News
title: Europe puts forward counter-proposal to Trump’s Ukraine plan

author: CNN
description: MIT researchers developed a new ultrasonic device that can harvest clean drinking water from the air in minutes. #CNN #News
title: See how researchers harvest water from the air

author: CNN
description: Police say Morgan Geyser, one of the teens involved in the 2014 Slender Man stabbing, cut off her GPS monitor and vanished. She was found more than 150 miles away at an Illinois truck stop.
title: ‘Slender Man’ attacker goes missing for 24 hours

author: CNN
description: Members of a local winter swimming club braved freezing temperatures in Russia's Yakutsk, Reuters reports. #CNN #news
title: Swimmers brave the ice in Russia

author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump lashed out at Ukraine’s leaders Sunday for what he described as a lack of gratitude, as top US officials meet with a delegation from Kyiv to broker an end to the Russia-Ukraine war. “UKRAINE ‘LEADERSHIP’ HAS EXPRESSED ZERO GRATITUDE FOR OUR EFFORTS, AND EUROPE CONTINUES TO BUY OIL FROM RUSSIA,” Trump wrote in a post on Truth Social.

John Berman speaks with CNN senior reporter Daniel Dale, who fact-checks Trump's claims, and Sara Sidner speaks with CNN global affairs analyst Brett McGurk about the status of the Ukraine peace talks in Geneva. #CNN #News
title: 'This claim is wildly inaccurate': CNN fact-checks Trump on Ukraine gratitude

author: CNN
description: The Trump administration could have expanded authority to take action in Venezuela starting Monday, as the US designates Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro and his government allies as members of a foreign terrorist organization.  #CNN #News
title: Trump admin designates Maduro as member of a foreign terrorist organization

author: CNN
description: Several people have been killed after Russian attacks on Ukraine's second-largest city, Kharkiv. The strikes come as Secretary of State Marco Rubio touts "tremendous progress" in peace negotiations. #cnn #news
title: Ukraine hit with strikes as peace talks ongoing

author: CNN
description: The parents of a family of five who were living off-grid in an Italian forest have been separated from their children after a court order. Tens of thousands of people have signed an online petition to reunite the family after the story captivated Italy. CNN's Barbie Nadeau reports. #CNN #news
title: Why these kids in Italy were taken from their parents

author: CNN
description: The Israeli military has struck Lebanon's capital Beirut for the first time in months, killing Hezbollah's chief of staff among others. CNN's Nic Robertson has more. #cnn #news #israel #lebanon #hezbollah
title: Israel strikes Lebanon's capital for first time in months

author: CNN
description:
In an exclusive interview, CNN's Omar Jimenez speaks with Marimar Martinez, a United States citizen who was accused of ramming the vehicle of a Customs and Border Protection agent in Chicago before he shot her several times. A judge dismissed charges against Martinez after a reversal by federal prosecutors in one of the most high-profile cases connected to Operation Midway Blitz in Chicago.

#CNN #News
title: Woman shot by border patrol five times speaks out

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Hanako Montgomery gains rare access to the mansion of an accused Chinese crime boss, Huang Zhiyang, who authorities say was involved in large-scale human trafficking and scams affecting thousands of people in Asia. #cnn #news #scam #trafficking #zhiyang
title: CNN tours Chinese crime boss mansion

author: CNN
description: Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro danced to a remix of his own "No War, Yes Peace" speech amid heightened tensions with the US.
title: Venezuela's Maduro dances to 'No War, Yes Peace' song

author: CNN
description: The Christian Association of Nigeria has reported more than 300 students were abducted from a Catholic school in northern Nigeria, some as young as ten years old. CNN's Larry Madowo reports.
title: Hundreds of students kidnapped from Catholic school in Nigeria
